SIMPLE: indusium
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indusium
<hw>In*du"si*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Indusia</plw> <pr>(-⟦adot⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., an under garment,
fr. <ets>induere</ets> to put on: cf. F. <ets>indusie</ets> the covering
of the seed spots of ferns.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
collection of hairs united so as to form a sort of cup, and inclosing
the stigma of a flower.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The immediate covering
of the fruit dots or sori in many ferns, usually a very thin scale
attached by the middle or side to a veinlet.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A
peculiar covering found in certain fungi.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Industrial</ent>⟦br⟧
